One thing that is lacking in twitter here is the mythos of the hacker. Mysterious, autistic, unseen, in hold of magical powers. It is the piracy of today in more ways than one - it is absolute freedom, even one from identity. Illegal activity, heroic deeds, hentai, highwaymanism

The show Mr. Robot did a good job of enchanting normies with the hacker mystique by presenting one as a central figure of a story instead of the sidenerd... I have always had tremendous love of this new craft, the left-hand path of programmism, Robin Hood in woods of pixels
